      <h2 class="section-title"><span>Abstract</span><span class="sec-num">§ 01</span></h2>

      <p class="lede">
        The AURA Lab, founded in Fall 2024 at William &amp; Mary, advances
        research at the intersection of <em>efficiency</em>,
        <em>automation</em>, and <em>explainability</em> in software
        engineering<a href="#sn-1" class="sn-ref">1</a>. Our mission is to
        design innovative and responsible AI-driven solutions that improve
        developer productivity while addressing the harder problems sitting
        underneath that promise &mdash; transparency about how a model
        reached a suggestion, and resource efficiency for the people who
        have to run it.
      </p>

      <blockquote class="statement">
        <p>
          Through rigorous methods, open collaboration, and a commitment to
          impactful work, the AURA Lab contributes practical advances in
          AI-supported software engineering for academia, industry, and
          society.
        </p>
      </blockquote>

      <div class="equation">
        <span class="lhs">AURA</span>
        <span class="eq">=</span>
        <span class="fn">f</span>(
          <span class="arg">transparency</span><span class="arg-sep">,</span>
          <span class="arg">efficiency</span><span class="arg-sep">,</span>
          <span class="arg">agency</span><span class="arg-sep">,</span>
          <span class="arg">autonomy</span>
        )
        <div class="equation-caption">
          <span class="eq-label">Eq. 1</span>
          The four axes the lab optimizes for, in the order they tend to be
          traded off against one another.
        </div>
      </div>
