    <!-- Agenda -->
    <section id="agenda">
      <h2 class="section-title"><span>Research Agenda</span><span class="sec-num">§ 02</span></h2>

      <p>
        We work where program analysis, machine learning, and human
        judgment meet. Large language models have changed what is possible
        in software engineering automation; they have not changed the
        engineering questions that matter &mdash; can the developer inspect
        the suggestion, afford to run the model, and trust the result on a
        legacy codebase that no one fully remembers writing?<a href="#sn-2" class="sn-ref">2</a>
      </p>

      <p>
        Our agenda is organized around four primary avenues and one
        supporting direction. Each is empirical first: we publish at venues
        that demand reproducible benchmarks and concrete deltas on real
        workloads, not just narrative claims about capability.
      </p>

