    <!-- Avenues -->
    <section id="avenues">
      <h2 class="section-title"><span>Five Research Avenues</span><span class="sec-num">§ 03</span></h2>

      <ol class="avenues">
        <li>
          <h4>Explainability &amp; Interpretability</h4>
          <p>Methods that reveal how code models reason &mdash; rationales, traces, generated tests &mdash; so developers can inspect, trust, and debug automation rather than accept it on faith.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h4>Efficiency &amp; Resource-Aware Automation</h4>
          <p>Quantization, distillation, and parameter-efficient fine-tuning to deliver low-latency, memory-light, cost-aware automation measured on real workloads with reproducible metrics<a href="#sn-3" class="sn-ref">3</a>.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h4>Multi-Agent LLMs for SE</h4>
          <p>Role-aligned agents that plan, code, test, and review, coordinated to produce coherent, end-to-end developer assistance rather than disconnected single-shot completions.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h4>Neurosymbolic AI for SE</h4>
          <p>Hybrid pipelines pairing LLMs with program analysis and constraints to produce interpretable, checkable fixes, tests, and designs<a href="#sn-4" class="sn-ref">4</a>.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="secondary">
          <h4>Task-Aware Code Automation <small>supporting direction</small></h4>
          <p>From issues, diffs, and traces to concise summaries, TODOs, and plans; models that reduce developer toil with actionable, repo-aware guidance.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

